{
  "texts": [
    "Image fusion This technique consists of generating a synthetic image by suitably combining or fusing two or more real images that exhibit specific features (e.g., a pedestrian or a face image).",
    "For Re-Id, two different fusion techniques have been proposed.",
    "One consists of linearly interpolating two randomly selected training images to obtain a larger training set and improve the generalisation capability (Li et al. 2020).",
    "The other technique aims at forcing the model to focus on important features, e.g., the image foreground (Yaghoubi et al. 2021); to this aim, two images are selected according to some constraints in terms of aspect ratio, pose and viewpoint, and are then fused to obtain a new pedestrian image with, e.g., mixed lower-or upper-body appearance with respect to the original images, or the full-body of one pedestrian over the background of the other one.",
    "Image fusion techniques have also been used in face recognition."
  ]
}